description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Medical Secretary - Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;25 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Medical Secretary who has excellent interpersonal skills and a calm methodical approach to provide essential secretarial/administration duties to a team of Consultants &amp; their wider team within our Obstetrics and Gynaecology department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have high attention to detail ideally have an understanding of Dictate IT, although training will be provided, you will type results letters and occasional reports, and occasional taking and transcribing minutes, diary management, arranging meetings, pulling notes, filing, distribution of post, using hospital PAS system and other databases and liaison with other healthcare professionals. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have responsibility for your assigned Consultants’ clinics as the NHS currently undergoes its largest piece of transformation work in how we now provide effective clinics.   &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to have an excellent telephone manner, be courteous and efficient and have exceptional working knowledge of Word, Excel spreadsheets, emails, use of an electronic diary etc.  A good sound knowledge of RTT and Cancer standards would be an advantage.   &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is varied and at times can be busy. You will be expected to cross cover for your colleagues in times of annual leave and sickness, so an ability to multitask is essential.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;For an informal discussion contact Anthony O’Mahoney on 01483 571122 ext 3287, o&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;r email on Anthony.o’mahoney@nhs.net&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date:  16th November &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date:  TBC &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
